external_knowledge:
- "Roles that are as common as the bread and butter of society" refers to roles that represent at least 50% of the population;
- "Stands tall as the highest earner" refers to the role with the highest average salary;
- "Standard workweek" refers to the typical 40-hour workweek.

- 'Seasoned educators' refers to employees who have been in their roles for at least 6 months;
- 'Performance' is represented by the average rating from performance reviews;
- 'Health' is represented by the average blood pressure from health metrics.

- 'tending to the seeds of knowledge' refers to working in the education sector;
- 'the average time spent' corresponds to the average actual hours worked;
- 'a modest 30 hours to a dedicated 80 hours' specifies the range of actual hours worked.

- 'Crossed the threshold of 21 years' refers to a minimum age of 21 or older;
- 'Shine with an average salary surpassing the $50,000 mark' means the average salary is greater than $50,000;
- 'When their hard-earned hours are accounted for' indicates the salary calculation is based on actual hours worked, adjusted to a standard 40-hour work week.

- 'Top-rated' refers to employees with the highest performance rating in their role;
- 'Low infection rate' refers to roles with an actual infection rate less than 10%;
- 'Past year' refers to the last 12 months from the current date.

sql:
SELECT AVG(average_salary) AS average_salary_medical_doctors
FROM roles
WHERE name = 'medical doctor' AND min_age <= 30;

external_knowledge:
- 'Highly rated' refers to employees with ratings of 'excellent' or 'satisfactory';
- 'Healthy blood pressure' is defined as a metric value less than 120;
- 'Healthy cholesterol' is defined as a metric value less than 200.

- "Highly active" refers to employees with more than 10 logged activities;
- "Regularly monitored their health metrics" refers to employees with more than 5 health metric records;
- Performance ratings are converted to numerical values: 1 for 'excellent', 0.75 for 'satisfactory', and 0.5 for 'unsatisfactory'.
